<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="163" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[140,1108,1574,1672]" pageId="14" pageNumber="163">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[140,267,1574,1600]" pageId="14" pageNumber="163">
<emphasis box="[140,262,1574,1600]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="163" reason="1">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The male differs from other species of the genus by the shape of the broad median apophysis, with the apical lobe narrowing abruptly at the tip and the basal lobe with a barbed, forward pointing projection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
