<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="164" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[140,1108,1011,1672]" pageId="15" pageNumber="164">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[185,320,1011,1037]" pageId="15" pageNumber="164">
<emphasis box="[185,315,1011,1037]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="164" reason="1">Etymology</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin for a small hook or barb and refers to the shape of the projection on the posterior lobe of the median apophysis.
</paragraph>
